<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
This species is named for the biogeographic region in which it is found following the boundaries of 
<bibRefCitation author="Croom, M" journalOrPublisher="Marine Region 15: Northeast Pacific. A global representative system of marine protected areas" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="55 - 107" refId="B5" refString="Croom, M, Wolotira, R, Henwood, W, 1995. . Marine Region 15: Northeast Pacific. A global representative system of marine protected areas Vol. 4: 55 - 107" volume="Vol. 4" year="1995">Croom et al. (1995)</bibRefCitation>
more closely than those of 
<bibRefCitation author="Valentine, JW" journalOrPublisher="Limnology and Oceanography" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="198 - 211" publicationUrl="10.4319/lo.1966.11.2.0198" refId="B35" refString="Valentine, JW, 1966. Numerical analysis of marine molluscan ranges on the extratropical northeastern Pacific shelf. Limnology and Oceanography 11: 198 - 211, DOI: 10.4319/lo.1966.11.2.0198" title="Numerical analysis of marine molluscan ranges on the extratropical northeastern Pacific shelf." url="10.4319/lo.1966.11.2.0198" volume="11" year="1966">Valentine (1966)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fort Bragg to just south of Ventura Beach, California, USA.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">We did not obtain an SSU sequence from type material of this species. The SSU sequence in GenBank (KP903907) for this species is from another Monterey Peninsula site: Carmel River State Beach.</paragraph>
